                            <comment id="13017556" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 8 Apr 2011 17:25:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;50MB does seem rather large as a default; I would have thought 16MB would be plenty?&lt;br/&gt;
Perhaps we should make the default smaller.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be possible to add new methods which allowed the buffer size to be provided; however this would mean adding about 7 new methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately changing the buffersize to a variable would be thread-hostile: if two threads set different values, there is a timing window between setting the value and starting the copy method. This cannot be avoided.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a pity the class methods are all static ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One other possibility would be to allow the default to be set by using a System Property; this could be thread-safe, but the value could not be changed once set.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13018285" author="niallp" created="Mon, 11 Apr 2011 11:12:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we should just reduce the size to fix the problem Igor found - so 30M is the nearest (rounded)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13030736" author="abrand@esca.fr" created="Mon, 9 May 2011 13:47:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I attached a patch setting the chunk at 30MB since I&apos;m also affected by this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13030825" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 9 May 2011 17:29:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed to 30MB&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
